title: [Western Waterway, Harbor]
description: Anchored for the evening, a small boat bedecked with bright orange and yellow sails remains stationary in the gentle ocean current.  The sound of the water lapping against its sides is lulling, and the single lantern occupying the deck casts a pallid light across the darkened ocean surface.
paths: Obvious paths: north, northeast, east, southeast, south, west
